We have section 5.3 (IP based protocol mapping) that defines an OpenAPI protocol mapping that can be used for HTTP, along with an example and formal CDDL definition. This is normative in the current draft. 
Here's what the example looks like: 
``` json
{
 "sdfProperty": {
   "heartrate": {
     "sdfProtocolMap": {
      "openapi": {
         "operationRef": "https://example.com/openapi.json#/paths/~1heartrate~1{id}~1current",
         "$ref": "https://example.com/openapi.json#/components/schema/HeartRate/properties/pulse"
       }
     }
   }
 }
} 
```

There were some concerns in the IETF124 meeting regarding this. @cabo's suggestion was to make this particular mapping non-normative and move the example to the appendix.

One of the suggestions we proposed to keep it normative was to use `http` as the protocol and have a type field that says that we are using openapi to map it. 
```diff
 {
   "sdfProperty": {
     "heartrate": {
       "sdfProtocolMap": {
-        "openapi": {
+        "http": {
+          "type": "openapi",
           "operationRef": "https://example.com/openapi.json#/paths/~1heartrate~1{id}~1current",
           "$ref": "https://example.com/openapi.json#/components/schema/HeartRate/properties/pulse"
         }
       }
     }
   }
 } 
```

@elear suggested that we take a to digest this. We can use this issue to discuss on it further.

pulls.body:
This PR fixes the CDDL definitions in the draft to include the `sdfProtocolMap`, `ble`, `zigbee`, and `openapi` keys.

Also, added a way to add separate read/write mappings to a single SDF property.

For example, we can have a mapping like this which maps the read to the GET and write to the PUT:
``` json
{
  "sdfProtocolMap": {
    "openapi": {
      "operationRef": "https://example.com/openapi.json#/paths/~1heartrate~1{id}~1current",
      "$ref": "https://example.com/openapi.json#/components/schema/HeartRate/properties/pulse"
    }
  }
}
```

Or a more specific one: 
``` json
{
  "sdfProtocolMap": {
    "openapi": {
      "read": {
        "operationRef": "https://example.com/openapi.json#/paths/~1heartrate~1{id}~1current/get",
        "$ref": "https://example.com/openapi.json#/components/schema/HeartRate/properties/pulse"
      },
      "write": {
        "operationRef": "https://example.com/openapi.json#/paths/~1heartrate~1{id}~1current/post",
        "$ref": "https://example.com/openapi.json#/components/schema/HeartRate/properties/pulse"
      }
    }
  }
}

```
